description: To knowingly say something that is untrue.
name: LIE (MISLEAD)

description: To put something in a place where it will be harder to discover or out of sight.
name: HIDE (CONCEAL)

description: An outer garment covering the upper torso and arms.
name: COAT

description: A hard, amorphous, inorganic, usually transparent, brittle substance made by fusing silicates, sometimes borates and phosphates, with certain basic oxides and then rapidly cooling to prevent crystallization.
name: GLASS

description: Edible, starchy seeds of the grass family (Graminae) usable as food by man and his livestock.
name: GRAIN

description: A very large and widespread family of Monocotyledoneae, with more than 10.000 species, most of which are herbaceous, but a few are woody. The stems are jointed, the long, narrow leaves originating at the nodes. The flowers are inconspicuous, with a much reduced perianth, and are wind-pollinated or cleistogamous.
name: GRASS

description: A plant-eating insect with long back legs that can jump very high and makes a sharp high noise using its back legs or wings.
name: GRASSHOPPER

description: An inlet of the sea of large areal proportions, more indented than a bay and generally more enclosed.
name: GULF

description: Precipitation in the form of balls or irregular lumps of ice.
name: HAIL

description: Area of water next to the coast, often surrounded by thick walls, where ships and boats can be sheltered.
name: PORT

description: The amount or measure of the crop gathered in a season.
name: HARVEST

description: A form of energy that is transferred by a difference in temperature: it is equal to the total kinetic energy of the atoms or molecules of a system.
name: HEAT

description: The level of water when the tide is at its highest level.
name: HIGH TIDE

description: A natural elevation of the land surface, usually rounded.
name: HILL

description: A large animal with four legs of the Equus caballus species which people ride on or use for carrying things or pulling vehicles.
name: HORSE

description: A place where people who are ill or injured are treated and taken care of by doctors and nurses.
name: HOSPITAL

description: The dense substance formed by the freezing of water to the solid state; it commonly occurs in the form of hexagonal crystals.
name: ICE

description: The inclined surface of any part of the Earth's surface, as a hillslope; also, a broad part of a continent descending toward an ocean, as the Pacific slope. (Source: BJGEO)
name: PRECIPICE

description: Any living organism characterized by voluntary movement, the possession of cells with noncellulose cell walls and specialized sense organs enabling rapid response to stimuli, and the ingestion of complex organic substances such as plants and other animals.
name: ANIMAL

description: A class of the Arthropoda typically having a segmented body with an external chitinous covering, a pair of compound eyes, a pair of antennae, three pairs of mouthparts, and two pairs of wings.
name: INSECT

description: A malleable ductile silvery-white ferromagnetic metallic element with symbol Fe and atomic number 26, occurring principally in haematite and magnetite. It is widely used for structural and engineering purposes.
name: IRON

description: A land mass, especially one smaller than a continent, entirely surrounded by water.
name: ISLAND

description: A body of water cut off from the open sea by coral reefs or sand bars.
name: LAGOON

description: An enclosed body of water, usually but not necessarily fresh water, from which the sea is excluded.
name: LAKE

description: A device that produces light, such as an electric lamp.
name: LAMP

description: A specified geographical tract of the Earth's surface including all its attributes, comprising its geology, superficial deposits, topography, hydrology, soils, flora and fauna, together with the results of past and present human activity, to the extent that these attributes exert a significant influence on the present and future land utilization. (Source: WHIT)
name: LAND

description: A heavy toxic bluish-white metallic element with symbol Pb and atomic number 82 that is highly malleable; occurs principally as galena and is used in alloys, accumulators, cable sheaths, paints, and as a radiation shield.
name: LEAD (CHEMICAL ELEMENT)

description: The main organ of photosynthesis and transpiration in higher plants, usually consisting of a flat green blade attached to the stem directly or by a stalk.
name: LEAF

description: The dressed or tanned hide of an animal, usually with the hair removed.
name: LEATHER

description: Electromagnetic radiation that is capable of causing a visual sensation. (Source: CED)
name: LIGHT (RADIATION)

description: Cattle, horses, and similar animals kept for domestic use especially on a farm.
name: LIVESTOCK

description: Any reptile of the suborder Lacertilia, especially those of the family Lacertidae, typically having an elongated body, four limbs, and a small tail: includes the gechos, iguanas, chameleons, monitors, and slow worms.
name: LIZARD

description: Place of commercial activity in which articles are bought and sold.
name: MARKET

description: The edible flesh of animals, especially that of mammals.
name: MEAT

description: The whitish fluid secreted by the mammary gland for the nourishment of the young; composed of carbohydrates, proteins, fats, mineral salts, vitamins, and antibodies.
name: MILK

description: A mill is a device that breaks solid materials into smaller pieces by grinding, crushing, or cutting.
name: MILL

description: Any plant of the class Bryophyta, occurring in nearly all damp habitats.
name: MOSS

description: Single-track, two-wheeled motor vehicle.
name: MOTORCYCLE

description: A feature of the earth's surface that rises high above the base and has generally steep slopes and a relatively small summit area.
name: MOUNTAIN

description: A mixture of clay and/or silt with water to form a plastic mass with a particle size preponderantly below 0.06 mm diameter. It is deposited in low-energy environments in lakes, estuaries and lagoons. It may also be deposited in deep-sea environments. (Source: WHIT)
name: MUD

description: An organism belonging to a family of Basidiomycetes that are characterized by the production of spores on gills.
name: MUSHROOM

description: The artistic organisation of sounds or tones that expresses ideas and emotions through the elements of rhythm, melody, harmony and tonal colour.
name: MUSIC

description: The fact or an instance of feeling the lack of something.
name: NEED (NOUN)

description: Any tree of the genus Quercus in the order Fagales, characterized by simple, usually lobed leaves, scaly winter buds, a star-shaped pith, and its fruit, the acorn, which is a nut; the wood is tough, hard, and durable, generally having a distinct pattern.
name: OAK

description: The mass of water occupying all of the Earth's surface not occupied by land, but excluding all lakes and inland seas.
name: OCEAN

description: The incombustible matter remaining after a substance has been incinerated.
name: ASH

description: A mixture of pigment and a vehicle, such as oil or water, that together form a liquid or paste that can be applied to a surface to provide an adherent coating that imparts colour, protects the surface and/or gives the surface different features.
name: PAINT (PIGMENTS)

description: Felted or matted sheets of cellulose fibers, formed on a fine-wire screen from a dilute water suspension, and bonded together as the water is removed and the sheet is dried.
name: PAPER

description: Land covered with grass or herbage and grazed by or suitable for grazing by livestock.
name: PASTURE

description: A comparatively volatile liquid bitumen composed principally of hydrocarbon, with traces of sulphur, nitrogen or oxygen compounds; can be removed from the earth in a liquid state.
name: PETROLEUM

description: A mammal belonging to the Pinnipedia, an order of aquatic placental mammals having a streamlined body and limbs specialized as flippers: includes seals, sea lions, and the walrus.
name: SEAL

description: An extensive, broad tract of level or rolling, almost treeless land with a shrubby vegetation, usually at a low elevation.
name: PLAIN

description: Any living organism that synthesizes its food from inorganic substances, possesses cellulose cell walls, responds slowly and often permanently to a stimulus, lacks specialized sense organs and nervous system, and has no powers of locomotion.
name: PLANT (VEGETATION)

description: A polymeric material (usually organic) of large molecular weight which can be shaped by flow; usually refers to the final product with fillers, plasticizers, pigments, and stabilizers included (versus the resin, the homogeneous polymeric starting material); examples are polyvinyl chloride, polyethylene, and urea-formaldehyde.
name: PLASTIC

description: A substance which, when ingested, inhaled, or absorbed, or when applied to, injected into, or developed within the body, in relatively small amounts, may cause injury, harm, or destruction to organs, tissue, or life.
name: POISON

description: Branch of the government which is charged with the preservation of public order, the promotion of public health and safety, and the prevention, detection, and punishment of crimes.
name: POLICE

description: The amount of money paid per unit for a good or service.
name: PRICE

description: Precipitation in the form of liquid water drops with diameters greater than 0.5 millimetres.
name: RAIN (PRECIPITATION)

description: Any of various types of tall stiff grass-like plants growing together in groups near water.
name: REED

description: A line of rocks in the tidal zone of a coast, submerged at high water but partly uncovered at low water.
name: REEF

description: The expression of man's belief in and reverence for a superhuman power recognized as the creator and governor of the universe.
name: RELIGION

description: A cell or several cells connected together, each cell containing the essentials for producing voltaic electricity.
name: BATTERY

description: An open, curving indentation made by the sea or a lake into a coastline.
name: BAY

description: Any of a class of solid or semisolid organic products of natural or synthetic origin with no definite melting point, generally of high molecular weight.
name: RESIN

description: Any of the membranous-winged insects which compose the superfamily Apoidea in the order Hymenoptera characterized by a hairy body and by sucking and chewing mouthparts.
name: BEE

description: A stream of water which flows in a channel from high ground to low ground and ultimately to a lake or the sea, except in a desert area where it may dwindle away to nothing.
name: RIVER

description: A long piece of hard ground that people can drive along from one place to another.
name: ROAD

description: Any aggregate of minerals that makes up part of the earth's crust. It may be unconsolidated, such as sand, clay, or mud, or consolidated, such as granite, limestone, or coal.
name: ROCK

description: Any of the relatively small placental mammals that constitute the order Rodentia, having constantly growing incisor teeth specialized for gnawing.
name: RODENT

description: The absorbing and anchoring organ of a vascular plant; it bears neither leaves nor flowers and is usually subterranean.
name: ROOT

description: A loose material consisting of small mineral particles, or rock and mineral particles, distinguishable by the naked eye; grains vary from almost spherical to angular, with a diameter range from 1/16 to 2 millimeters.
name: SAND

description: Before the expected time.
name: EARLY

description: An institution or building at which children and young people receive education.
name: SCHOOL

description: Opening in the lower half of a human face which is used for food ingestion and articulation.
name: MOUTH

description: Substance that human and animal bodies release from time to time as a little pile of waste remaining from digestion, after it has been collected in the colon.
name: FAECES (EXCREMENT)

description: To excrete faeces from one's body through the anus.
name: SHIT (DEFECATE)

description: A tool for felling trees or chopping wood consisting of a heavy metallic head flattened to a blade on one side, and which is attached to a usually wooden handle.
name: AXE

description: Facial hair of humans on the chin, cheeks and jaw.
name: BEARD

description: Visually dazzling.
name: BRIGHT

description: To end up in two or more pieces, which can't easily be reassembled.
name: BREAK (DESTROY OR GET DESTROYED)

description: To damage beyond use or repair.
name: DESTROY

description: One side of a leaf of a book or manuscript.
name: SIDE

description: A human being.
name: PERSON

description: To have rightful possession of property, goods or capital.
name: OWN

description: To reach, make, or come to a decision about something.
name: DECIDE

description: Requiring little skill or effort; posing no difficulty.
name: EASY

description: Not any thing.
name: NOTHING

description: A biological organ that extracts oxygen from the air.
name: LUNG

description: In the position or interval that separates two things.
name: BETWEEN

description: The part furthest in the direction toward which an unsupported object would fall.
name: BOTTOM

description: One of the four equal periods into which the year is divided by the equinoxes and solstices, resulting from the apparent movement of the sun north and south of the equator during the course of the earth's orbit around it. These periods (spring, summer, autumn and winter) have their characteristic weather conditions in different regions, and occur at opposite times of the year in the N and S hemispheres.
name: SEASON

description: To transport toward somewhere; to take something or somebody with oneself somewhere.
name: BRING

description: Indicates the source or provenance.
name: FROM

description: To get or obtain an item; to come into the possession of something.
name: GET

description: To move from a place to another that is further away.
name: GO

description: To stir two or more substances together.
name: STIR

description: To contain or hold; have within.
name: CONTAIN

description: Showing good judgement or the benefit of experience.
name: WISE

description: Feeling mentally uncomfortable because something is missing or wrong.
name: SAD

description: To lift and bring to somewhere else; to transport by lifting.
name: CARRY

description: With low speed.
name: SLOW

description: To take hold of, especially in the hands, so as to seize or restrain or stop the motion of.
name: CATCH

description: In a near future.
name: SOON

description: Not dirty.
name: CLEAN

description: To ascend; to go up.
name: GO UP (ASCEND)

description: Having an absolute or (more often) relative lack of light.
name: DARK

description: To recall from memory.
name: REMEMBER

description: To emit light.
name: SHINE

description: To pass on knowledge and skills.
name: TEACH

description: A circular object that spins around a central axe thereby allowing relatively low-friction movement.
name: WHEEL

description: Having a vertical extent greater than the average; Having the upper end, tip, top, head, etc. a long way up; Having a great vertical extent (often greater than the horizontal extent); High.
name: TALL

description: Possessing in abundance a particular trait.
name: RICH

description: To take possession of property belonging to another without the consent of this owner; most typically when not observed, rather than by force.
name: STEAL

description: A mature fertilized plant ovule, consisting of an embryo and its food store surrounded by a protective seed coat (testa).
name: SEED

description: To utter a sudden and loud outcry.
name: SHOUT

description: a low, guttural sound of frustration
name: GROAN

description: Having the taste characteristic of sugar or honey.
name: SWEET

description: To give money in exchange for goods or services.
name: PAY

description: To encounter something by accident or after searching for it.
name: FIND

description: Something positive that happens to someone by chance.
name: GOOD LUCK

description: In a position comparatively close to the ground.
name: LOW

description: The application of violent force to someone or something.
name: ATTACK

description: A position or area in a space.
name: PLACE (POSITION)

description: To look at and interpret letters or other information that is written.
name: READ

description: An older person (usually considered to be above the age of 60).
name: OLD PERSON

description: A certain duration of time, a period of time
name: WHILE

description: What one or ones (of those mentioned or implied).
name: WHICH

description: Having no predecessor. The ordinal number corresponding to one.
name: FIRST

description: A period of time at the beginning of the day shortly before sunrise during which the light gradually becomes stronger.
name: DAWN

description: Any reptile of the suborder Serpentes, typically having a scaly cylindrical limbless body, fused eyelids, and a jaw modified for swallowing large prey.
name: SNAKE

description: Any one of various liquids for drinking.
name: BEVERAGE

description: belonging to the second person that is addressed by the first person.
name: YOUR (SINGULAR)

description: To gain (success) through applied effort or work.
name: EARN

description: To create something by combining or assembling materials or parts or by changing it.
name: MAKE

description: A solitary, mainly nocturnal bird of prey, belonging to the order Strigiformes; it has large forward-facing eyes and ears and a hawk-like beak, and it can turn its head 180 degrees around.
name: OWL

description: A small, usually uncultivated area adjoining or within the precincts of a house or other building.
name: YARD

description: To start a fire or light a flame.
name: LIGHT (IGNITE)

description: That which is considered to exist as a separate entity, quality or concept.
name: THING

description: To give food.
name: FEED

description: A vessel propelled by engines or sails for navigating on the water, especially a large vessel that can not be carried aboard another, as distinguished from a boat.
name: SHIP

description: To operate a (motorized) vehicle (with wheels).
name: DRIVE

description: Extreme part.
name: END (OF SPACE)

description: The last or final part.
name: END (OF TIME)

description: Egg (either fertilized or not) from domesticated birds, most commonly hens, seen as food.
name: EGG

description: A flat, rigid, rectangular structure, fixed at right angles to a wall, and used to support, store or display objects.
name: SHELF

description: A place, especially a small building, for the retail sale of goods and services.
name: SHOP

description: A vehicle with two wheels in tandem, pedals connected to the rear wheel by a chain, handlebars for steering, and a saddlelike seat.
name: BICYCLE

description: To scatter or disperse seeds on a field.
name: SOW SEEDS

description: To go into.
name: ENTER

description: The event of moving to a lower position due to the effect of gravity.
name: DROP

description: A woody perennial plant, smaller than a tree, with several major branches arising from near the base of the main stem.
name: SHRUB

description: An establishment, either physical or virtual, that sells goods or services to the public.
name: STORE

description: A student under the supervision of a teacher or professor.
name: PUPIL (STUDENT)

description: To move or do something at a fast pace.
name: HURRY

description: To refuse strongly and solemnly to own or acknowledge.
name: DENY

description: To rely on for support; to be conditioned or contingent; to be connected with anything, as a cause of existence, or as a necessary condition.
name: DEPEND

description: A fastener consisting of a knob or disc that is passed through a slit in the adjacent material.
name: BUTTON

description: A long-legged, long-necked wading bird of the family Ardeidae.
name: HERON

description: A very ductile malleable brilliant greyish-white element with symbol Ar and atomic number 47 having the highest electrical and thermal conductivity of any metal.
name: SILVER

description: A loop of string or any other long flexible material which cannot be untied without pulling part of the string through the loops.
name: KNOT

description: To place something over or upon to conceal or protect.
name: COVER

description: In the open, not within a building.
name: OUTSIDE

description: The tissue forming the outer covering of the vertebrate body: it consists of two layers, the outermost of which may be covered with hair, scales, feathers, etc. It is mainly protective and sensory in function.
name: SKIN

description: (Of an object) To be of the right size and shape so as to match another object.
name: SUIT

description: To change the location of an object.
name: MOVE

description: The period in the menstrual cycle when the endometrium is shed when conception did not take place.
name: MENSTRUATION

description: A dead body.
name: CORPSE

description: Meal usually eaten at midday.
name: LUNCH

description: The structure covering a building.
name: ROOF

description: A piece of jewelry worn on the ear.
name: EARRING

description: An item of clothing intended to cover the head made from material hard enough to have a shape independant of the skull, and most commonly with a rim.
name: HAT

description: A clothing accessory, usually made of leather or heavy cloth, worn around the waist and used to support trousers or other articles of clothing.
name: BELT

description: To be in possession (of an object).
name: HAVE

description: An edible plant, Brassica oleracea, with many varieties.
name: CABBAGE

description: A musical instrument in the brass family.
name: TRUMPET

description: The part of the body from the neck to the groin excluding the head and limbs.
name: TRUNK OF TREE

description: A musical instrument of the woodwind family.
name: FLUTE

description: An aerosol, consisting of visible particles and gases, produced by the incomplete burning of carbon-based materials, such as wood and fossil fuels.
name: SMOKE (EXHAUST)

description: A seperate unit of a larger whole.
name: PART

description: Belonging to us; of us
name: OUR

description: An emotion experienced in anticipation of some specific pain or danger.
name: FEAR (FRIGHT)

description: An end to a struggle or contest that did not end in success.
name: DEFEAT

description: An end to a struggle or contest that did end in success.
name: VICTORY

description: The most common form of frozen precipitation, usually flakes or starlike crystals, matted ice needles, or combinations, and often rime-coated.
name: SNOW

description: Capable of producing great physical force.
name: STRONG

description: A large piece of fabric (as canvas) by means of which wind is used to propel a sailing vessel.
name: SAILCLOTH

description: To traverse or travel by ship on a body of water.
name: SAIL

description: A cleansing agent, manufactured in bars, granules, flakes, or liquid form, made from a mixture of the sodium salts of various fatty acids of natural oils and fats.
name: SOAP

description: A group of persons forming or belonging to a particular nation, class, ethnic group, country, family, etc.
name: PEOPLE

description: Prepared for immediate action or use.
name: READY

description: Someone who is not known.
name: STRANGER

description: To be at a temperature (as a liquid) where it moves into the gaseous phase.
name: BOIL (OF LIQUID)

description: A painful, local inflammation of the skin, caused by infection of a hair follicle. Usually, a hard core and pus are present.
name: BOIL (OF SKIN)

description: A utensil, usually tubular in form, containing ink used to write or make marks.
name: PEN

description: Fresh water salmon.
name: TROUT

description: The projection of a mammary gland from which, on female mammals, milk can be secreted.
name: NIPPLE

description: The male sex gland that produces sperm and male hormones, found in some types of animals.
name: TESTICLES

description: Either of the two opposable structures forming, or near the entrance to, the mouth.
name: JAW

description: The flexible and narrower connection between the forearm and the hand.
name: WRIST

description: The area between the pelvis and buttocks and the knee.
name: THIGH

description: One of the long curved bones which form the rib cage.
name: RIB

description: A lump at the front of the neck.
name: ADAM'S APPLE

description: A joint formed where the foot and the leg meet.
name: ANKLE

description: The major female reproductive organ of most mammals, including humans. It is a large muscle enveloping the phoetus during pregnancy.
name: WOMB

description: The body part that consists of a row of vertebrae, that support the head and torso and that forms a canal for nerves.
name: SPINE

description: A large cloth used for warmth and for sleeping.
name: BLANKET

description: Experienced and clever, professional.
name: SKILLED

description: to fall in globules or small portions, as water or other liquid.
name: DRIP (FALL IN GLOBULES)

description: An item of clothing worn on the lower part of the body and covering both legs separately.
name: TROUSERS

description: Migratory grasshoppers of the order Orthoptera of warm regions having short antennae.
name: LOCUST

description: In philosophical or religious belief the immaterial part of a human being.
name: SOUL

description: A person who is owned and forced to work, usually without pay, by another.
name: SLAVE

description: To act, to behave.
name: DO

description: To clothe oneself; to put on clothes.
name: DRESS UP

description: A body that has the authority to make and the power to enforce laws within a civil, corporate, religious, academic, or other organization or group.
name: GOVERNMENT

description: One of the two equal parts of a whole.
name: HALF

description: The third person plural of the personal pronoun that designates more than one person or animal, thing or idea which have already been mentioned previously.
name: THEY

description: Any of various deciduous trees or shrubs in the genus Salix.
name: WILLOW

description: An organ in the body, involved in digestion of food.
name: STOMACH

description: Young sheep.
name: LAMB

description: Any of various deciduous trees of the genus Populus.
name: POPLAR

description: Which quantity?
name: HOW MANY

description: A male person who practices magic or sorcery.
name: SORCERER

description: A female person who uses magic.
name: WITCH

description: Not sleeping.
name: AWAKE

description: A separation of a river, a road, etcetera.
name: BRANCH (BIFURCATION)

description: To tip laterally.
name: ROLL

description: (Procyon lotor) An omnivorous nocturnal mammal native to North America and Central America.
name: RACCOON

description: One of several parallel sloping beams that extend from the ridge to the wall-plate, to support the roof and its associated loads; the sloping top member of a roof truss, which carries the purlins.
name: RAFTER

description: Impure black carbon with oily compounds obtained from the incomplete combustion of resinous materials, oils, wood, or coal.
name: SOOT

description: The bottom or lowest part.
name: BASE

description: Any of various leguminous plants grown for their edible seeds and pods.
name: BEAN

description: To allow (something that one dislikes or disagrees with) to continue to exist or occur without interference; accept or undergo, often unwillingly.
name: ENDURE

description: The fleshy part of the human body that one sits on.
name: BUTTOCKS

description: A part of a book, a literary work etc. with a distinct content, set apart using typography.
name: CHAPTER

description: A hand tool used for driving screws.
name: SCREWDRIVER

description: Having the pure color of a clear sky; the primary color between green and violet in the visible spectrum, an effect of light with a wavelength between 450 and 500 nm.
name: BLUE

description: The physical structure of a dead animal or person.
name: REMAINS

description: To make a mistake.
name: ERR

description: Medium sized, black water bird from the family of the cormorants (Phalacrocoracidae), scientific name: Phalacrocorax carbo
name: CORMORANT

description: A spearlike weapon with a barbed head used in hunting whales and large fish.
name: FISHING SPEAR

description: Alcoholic beverage containing more than 20 percent alcohol.
name: LIQUOR

description: Any predatory silk-producing arachnid of the order Araneae, having four pairs of legs and a rounded unsegmented body consisting of abdomen and cephalothorax.
name: SPIDER

description: A category of things distinguished by a common characteristic or quality.
name: KIND (THING)

description: The intentional or premeditated killing of another person.
name: MURDER

description: A large carnivorous animal (Panthera tigris) of the cat family indigenous to Asia.
name: TIGER

description: Feeling the need to drink.
name: THIRSTY

description: A physiological need to drink.
name: THIRST

description: A place where ground water flows naturally from a rock or the soil onto the land surface or into a body of surface water.
name: SPRING (OF WATER)

description: An open area in a town, sometimes including the surrounding buildings.

description: A building or structure usually with stalls that is used to house and feed horses, cattle or other animals.
name: STABLE

description: Table for religious ceremonies.

description: A metal container used to boil any kind of liquid.

description: To hold under a lease or rental agreement of goods and services.

description: A general term for rock that is used in construction, either crushed for use as aggregate or cut into shaped blocks as dimension stone.
name: STONE

description: An atmospheric disturbance involving perturbations of the prevailing pressure and wind fields on scales ranging from tornadoes to extratropical cyclones; also the associated weather and the like. (Source: MGH)
name: STORM

name: STOVE

description: That which brings about any condition or produces any effect.

description: A sweet crystalline or powdered substance, white when pure, consisting of sucrose obtained mainly from sugar cane and sugar beets and used in many foods, drinks, and medicines to improve their taste.

description: To achieve a victory.

description: A garment for a hand, often extending to the wrist and sometimes up to the elbow, which either covers each finger individually, or separates the thumb from the other fingers.
name: GLOVE

description: The fruit of the banana tree.

description: The flat, sharp-edged part of a tool.
name: BLADE

description: The air inhaled and exhaled through the lungs.
